{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/0022225470A/1930052301/0393.xml":{"full_text":"EDITORIAL PAGE\nOF THE\nWhen and Where Was U. S. Navy Policy Surrendered?\nNot only did the Hoover Administration surrender at\nthe London naval conference the established naval\npolicy of the United States for the last nine years, but\nit seems to have surrendered that policy without the\nformality of a real struggle.\nThe American people were given to understand that\nthe administration would insist upon retaining the right\nto build at least 21 eight-inch gun cruisers.\nBut the Senate is now told by a reliable witness that\nthe delegation was asking its naval advisers to agree to\naccept 18 instead of 21 eight-inch gun ships'before the\nconference was two weeks old.\nAs early as February 5 last, the delegation was\n.warned by Admiral Jones, its ablest and most exper\nienced naval adviser, that a treaty which reduced the\nnumber of eight-inch gun cruisers below 21 for the\nUnited States would not meet the minimum defense\nrequirements of our national defense as estimated by\nour highest naval authorities.\nIn his warning at London to the delegation, which\nSaturday Half Holidays for\nCivil Service Employes\nThe first serious start toward Saturday half holidays through\nout the year for civil employes of the Federal and District gov\nernments has been made by the House Civil Service Committee\nin amending a bill passed by the Senate providing such holi\ndays for special classes of employes.\nThe House proposition, because of legislation pending before\nanother House committee, does not include employes of the pos\ntal service, Panama Canal and field employes of the Interior\nDepartment, but would include most of the 65,000 Federal\nworkers in Washington.\nWhat the outlook for the House bill may be is problematical,\nbut there is significance in the favorable action of the House\nCivil Service Committee.\nSummer Saturday half holidays for Government workers is\nnow wholly dependent upon the President\u2014a gift by Execu\ntive act. Definite legislation by Congress would take this mat\nter from presidential hands and settle a long fight for year\nround half holidays on Saturdays.\nHow liberal eventual legislation may be will depend upon the\nwording of any bill passed, and possibly upon executive inter\npretation afterward.\nIf Government and District workers are to be compelled to\nwork half an hour longer on five days of each week to make up\nfor the holiday time they would get, then there is doubt as to\nwhether they will gain anything. Many employes are willing\nto do this to obtain Saturday half holidays. Others are opposed.\nSmall Loans Law for District\nIs Much Needed\nThe hot fight in the District Committee of the House over\na \u201csmall loans\u2019\u2019 law for this city would indicate that another\nsession of Congress will pass without legislation.\nThere should be legislation, however, and the rate' of interest\nshould not be extortionate. It should give protection to bor\nrowers, but at the same time enable lenders to make reason\nable profits.\nWhat the rate should be ought to be readily determined by\nCongress from the experiences of American cities and States\nthat have had to settle this problem.\nThe Russell Sage Foundation stands for a maximum rate of\n31/2 P er cent P er or 42 P cr ccnt a y ear 11 ls claimed\nunlicensed loan sharks in this city and outside now exact far\nhigher interest than that and that they will continue these\nextortions unless checked by a law that will control them.\nThe contention over the interest rate is bitter. That has\nbeen the rule every time a loan bill came before Congress.\nThe cleavage is all the more interesting because each side\nearnestly insists that it is acting from the standpoint of pro\ntecting the poor.\nThe \u201cloan sharks\u2019\u2019 stir up much of the differences. They\ndo not want restrictions of any kind. If there must be a law\nhere they want an interest rate big eriough to guarantee large\nprofits. They emphasize the dangerous chances they take,\nyet there is no financial suffering among loan sharks. There\nis suffering and want among those who must pay dearly for\nsmall loans to tide them over critical periods.\nHearst Papers Advocate\n1. \u201cPeace and amity with all nations; entangling\nalliances with none,\u201d as advocated by George\nWashington.\n2. Proportional representation in the United .States\nSenate, no State to have less than two Senators.\nLegislation to enforce prompt constitutional reap\nportionment in the House of Representatives.\n3. A separate Department of the Army, of the Navy\nand of the Air Forces, all united under a Secretary\nof National Defense.\n4. Federal action to the limit of Federal powers to\nabolish illiteracy in the United States under a\nSecretary of Education.\n5. Election of Congress tn November. Installation\non the first of January following. Inauguration\nof the President first of January next after\nNovember election.\nWASHINGTONTIMES\nThe Family Tree By t. e. Powers\nM /CUthaT 1 OTOk ir/mv s\nj I FIERCE IT 10/\nL obl'i rm Jx- i J/\nXX I. WITH THAT.' 4 te A;Z\nu al\nV k Fol BRMKINq Tar K f X\n-x- 1 1 -rx TRAFFIC LAW.' <7\nX& Jr r \u2014-.X j Ux.\\ ft\n\u2019'\"l \u2014r* B am l 1\u2022\u2022\nW'| gfr\nqwAH Nou 515\n8020 Nou /yx/\u2019Fb (Ticket C\\\nDoht pinch f\nWHIPONTWJJL A -M -V/1 l I X 4KI MOR.E\noiHtt/ //walkers.\n-y b y r xLL-LI Cme netdsA L-. A, r _ u\nX Juddc V I\n3 X \\\\x\\ tern-X XXXXXyXxXXXXXXX\nXX X iHsifeAwswsx L 'ri\nxXt\nTHE MARRY-GO-ROUND By Helen Rowland\nWhat Is \u201cHumanism\u201d?\nEvery now and then some\nbody springs a brand new cult,\na brand new religion, a brand\nnew philosophy or a brand\nnew WORD on us.\nThe newest and most pop\nular word of the moment is\n\u201cHUMANISM.\u201d And you are\ngoing to hear a lot about it\nfor the next few years.\nIt comes as manna from\nheaven, just as we were ex\npiring of boredom froml the\nlong-overworked words \u201cPsycho\nanalysis. Self-expression,\u201d\n\"Sex\u201d and \u201cModernism.\u201d\n\u201cHumanism\u201d doesn't, mean\nwhat you probably think it\ndoes. It doesn't mean what\nDad means, or what Husband\nmeans, umen he says. \u201cI\u2019M only\nhuman!\u201d just after he has done\nsomething particularly inhuman\nor unhuman, or subhuman. Oh,\nquite the contrary!\nIt doesn\u2019t mean be kind to\nanimals, or love your neighbor,\nor pity the poor\u2014humanitari\nanist. That\u2019s only part of it.\nAs far as I can make out\nfrom the mass of muddled\nmisinformation on the subject,\nit means the Divinity of Man.\nIt means that being a Human\nBeing is the rarest privilege\nand the greatest responsibility\nin the universe-\nthe Administration suppressed until it was forced into\nthe record at Washington this week by Senator Johnson\nof California, Admiral Jones said:\n\u201cAs adviser to the American delegation I feel\ncompelled to .express an opinion as to the tentative\nplan of the American delegation. In my opinion\nsuch an allotment weakens us in sea power relatively.\n\u201cThe plan departs dangerously from the standard of\nparity accepted, in that tonnage in the type of cruiser\nmost useful to us is decreased and the tonnage in the\ntype of cruiser less useful to us is increased.\u201d\nYet a treaty along these exact lines was negotiated\nand that is the treaty which the American delegation\nsigned and brought back from London and is now\nurging the Senate to pass.\nAt the very time that the Administration in Wash\nington was giving the American people to understand\nthat the advice of Admiral Jones was being followed the\nAmerican delegation in London was not only ignoring\nIt means that in every\nHuman Being there is a drop\nof divinity, which endows him\nwith infinite, limitless possi\nbilities, and at the same time\nplaces upon him the response\nbility for living UP to and ful\nfilling those possibilities.\nKNOWLEDGE TEST\nMatch correctly:\n1. Guam Italy\n2. Minorca The Netherlands\n3. Madeira Spain\n4. Java Portugal\n5. Sicily United States\nDo you know:\n6. Who wrote \u201cWestward Ho\u201d?\n7. What President had a \u201ckitchen cabinet\"?\n8. What was the scene of the greatest gold rush the world\nhas ever known?\nS>. What has made smallpox practically disappear?\n10. What poet said.\n\u201c\u2019Tis better to have loved and lost\nThan never to have loved at all\u201d?\n11. What is a turnkey?\n12. For what was John Marshall famous?\n13. What is a trousseau?\n14. What is carbolic acid derived from'\nla. What nickname u given to the Himalayas?\nk \u00abl llagaab*\nWhich is some Large Order!\n\u201cNoblesse oblige\u2019\u2019 is the spirit\nof its teachings, meaning that\nnobility obliges you\u2014and you\nand you\u2014to develop all the\nhigher and finer things within\nyou to the ultimate degree.\nAnd WHAT a joyful relief\nhis advice, but flouting his warning and suppressing his\nevery recommendation.\nIt begins to look as if the established naval policy of\nthe United States for which President Coolidge fought\nat Genova was abandoned by President Hoover before\nthe American delegation ever left the United States for\nLondon.\nPerhaps that is why Prime Minister MacDonald\nassures the Senate that the British government hade\nthe United States \u201ctake parity brimming up and over\nflowing.\u201d\nPerhaps Mr. MacDonald knew that the Administration\nwould not insist upon more than the 18 eight-inch gun\ncruisers, which the British government was willing for\nthis country to build.\nIf the Senate will make a real examination of all the\npapers leading up to the London conference this\nimportant fact mav be brought to light. FOR IT IS\nIMPORTANT TO KNOW WHEN AND WHERE AND\nBY WHOM THE SUPINE SURRENDER MADE BY\nTHE UNITED STATES IN THE LONDON NA\\ AL\nTREATY WAS FIRST BEGUN.\nthat is. after all this chatter\nabout \u201cbeins yourself,\u201d which\nthus far has meant being your\nlowest self, and as much of a\nsavage and an egoist as you\ndared to be.\nIt looks as though \u2018\u2018Human\nism,\u201d If it works, might deliver\nus from jazz and from free\nlove and from modernistic\nfurniture and jungle dances\nand vulgarity and money grab\nbing\u2014and even from rumble\nseat petting and futuristic\n\u201cart.\u201d For, its ideal is the\nworship of the beautiful, the\nspiritual, the lovely and the\ninspiring!\nIt is the Great REVOLT\nagainst, the savagery and ma\nterialism of the last decade\u2014\nand perhaps it will bring us\nback to sanity! Maybe it will\nmake gentlemen of road hogs:\nthinkers and scholars of speed\nmaniacs: music lovers of jazz\nhoundM, and human beings of\nmoney grabbers! You never\ncan tell.\nYet. after all, \u201cHumanism\u201d\nis just a new name for some\nthing that is as old as civiliza\ntion. Marcus Aurelius preached\nand wrote it. Emerson wrote\nand taught it. And the poet\nsang it, when he said. \"Build\nthee mor* stately mansuyur eh\nmy soull* i i\nWASHINGTON, D.\nj MAY 23, 1930\nBathtubs\nA Few Facts About Them.\nThe Metropolitan Life Insurance Company discovers that\nbathing is a menace. It\u2019s not that water is dangerous, but that\nso many people slip, fall and injure themselves in getting into\nor out of tubs.\nThere are more non-fatal accidents in the home than any\nwhere else, the company finds, and there are more non-fatal\naccidents in bathtubs than anywhere else in the home.\nThat is the price that the cleanest nation on earth must pay,\nwe suppose, for being clean. There\u2019s not much to be done\nabout it. For every gain there is a corresponding loss, as\nEmerson pointed out in his essay on compensation, and others\nhave learned without reading Emerson.\nThe company's statistics also show an interesting tendency\nin American life\u2014namely, that every night is bath night now.\nOnly one-seventh of the accidents happen on Saturday. The\nothers were distributed pro rata through the rest of the week.\nStill another significant fact is that more tubs were installed\nin the last five years than in the preceding ten. The accident\nrate, however, has not increased in the same proportion.\nThough the company does not say so, it is a fair inference that\nthe bathtub gin industry has boomed. How else can you ex\nplain it?\nZyxx, Zzyzz and Zzzyn\nAnd the State of the Nation\nThere is a fascination about matters of no importance,\nwhich, we suppose, accounts for many things published in the\nguise of \u201cnews.\u201d\nHere, for example, is an item far more interesting to mil\nlions of Americans than the tariff, or the naval treaty, or farm\nrelief:\n\u201cPedro Zyxx holds the undisputed cellar position in\nthe new city directory in San Francisco, but he has\nnothing on Mr. Kanttules Xanthafulos when it comes\nto unusual names.\n\u201cChicago\u2019s telephone directory offers A. Zzynck as\nits parting shot. In the Manhattan (New York) tele\nphone directory Zebediah Z. Zzyz had the honors until\nR. Cantarrana Zzyzz and Margot Wilson Zzzyn had\ntelephones installed.\u201d\nThat won't settle the state of the nation or shape history.\nBut people will read about it where they will yawn over the\nPresident's latest address on the business outlook, or say\n\u201cYeah?\u201d to the sugar import duties.\nIt\u2019s all right with us, but what's the reason?\nListen, World!\nVictory!\nI held a great pearl in my won\ndering hand.\nIt shone serenely, with a warm,\nwhite flame\nLike moonlight\u2014pulsing\u2014pas\nsionately pale\u2014\nLike moonlight\u2014whose mysteri\nous strength and peace\nQuiet rebellion, heal our fear\nand hurt\u2014\nSo the pearl shone. And from\nit streamed a light\nAs though some glory burned\nwithin its heart.\nBUt. really, pain lay buried in\nthat pearl.\nPearls do not bloom in ecstasy,\nlike flowers.\nNor do they ripen through\nsweet suns, like fruit.\nA pearl's unearthly glow is\nborn of pain.\nPain, bedded deep in some poor\noyster\u2019s flesh.\nA vicious bit of grit it can't\ncast out,\nBut must endure as long as\nlife shall last.\nAnd so the oyster wastes no\ntime in strife.\nBut wraps its forces \u2019round\nabout that bain.\nAnd slowly, film by film, builds\nits defense.\nFolding its pain within bright\nveils of light.\nUntil, at last, there gleams the\nperfect pearL\nBy Elsie Robinson\nSo some brave souls make\nbeauty out of grief.\nPain comes to them\u2014a pain\nthey cannot rout.\nBut must endure until their day\nis done.\nAnd. for a while, it seems as if\nthat pain\nMust gnaw all life into a hol\nlow hell.\nThen slowly the hurt spirit\ngathers strength.\nRallies its forces \u2019round that\nagony,\nAnd. from its secret tears, be\ngins to weave\nA veil of courage, gentleness and\npeace.\nThin veils at first\u2014so thin they\nscarcely hide\nThe mortal hurt that lies be\nhind their film;\nBut, with each day, the gleam\ning wonder grows,\nUntil, at last, the agony is hid,\nAnd that great life glows warm\nly, like a pearl.\nShedding a healing light on\ndarker lives,\nAs though some miracle burned\nin its heart.\nSome secret joy, untainted by\nllfp\u2019S\nSO SOME BRAVE SOULS\nMAKE BEAUTY OUT OF\nGRIEF\nAND ROUND DEFEAT. BUILD\nWALLS OF UVXNO LIGHT.","height":"30314","width":"24387"}}
